CELL SUSPENSION ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
SPECIMEN FROM ORGANISM ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
CELL SUSPENSION NAME: A short, descriptive name for the biomaterial that need not be unique.
CELL SUSPENSION DESCRIPTION: A general description of the biomaterial.
SUPPLEMENTARY FILES: A list of filenames of biomaterial-level supplementary files.
INSDC ID: An International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC) sample accession.
GENUS SPECIES (Required): The scientific binomial name for the species of the suspension.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
SELECTED CELL TYPE: The cell type(s) selected to be present in the suspension.
SELECTED CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession.
SELECTED CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLO: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field.
ESTIMATED CELL COUNT: Estimated number of cells in the suspension.
PERCENT CELL VIABILITY: Percent of cells determined to be viable.
CELL VIABILITY METHOD: The method by which cell viability was determined.
DISSOCIATION PROTOCOL ID (Required): A unique ID for the protocol.
ENRICHMENT PROTOCOL ID (Required): A unique ID for the protocol.

GENOTYPE: For example: DRB1 0401 protective allele; HLA-B*3901 allele
BIOSAMPLES ID: Enter ID if sample has been archived. ID can be from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI and must start with SAMD, SAMN, or SAME, respectively. For example: SAMN00000000
INSDC ID: Enter accession if sample has been archived. Accession can be from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI and must start with DRS, SRS, or ERS, respecitvely. For example: SRS0000000
GENUS SPECIES (Required): For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
GENUS SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLOGY ID: For example: Homo sapiens; Mus musculus
SELECTED CELL TYPE: For example: bone marrow hematopoietic cell; cardiac muscle cell
SELECTED CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY LABEL ONTOLO: For example: bone marrow hematopoietic cell; cardiac muscle cell
ESTIMATED CELL COUNT: Enter 1 for well-based assays. For example: 1; 2100
PERCENT CELL VIABILITY: Enter a single number. Average value is acceptable. For example: 98.7
CELL VIABILITY METHOD: For example: Fluorescein diacetate hydrolysis; ATP test
DISSOCIATION PROTOCOL ID (Required): Protocol ID should have no spaces.
ENRICHMENT PROTOCOL ID (Required): Protocol ID should have no spaces.
